comments: Plumlee (DET) engages and disengages with Davis (LAL) as they move toward the perimeter.
Grant (DET) legally contests Davis's (LAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Caruso (LAL) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Jackson's (DET) arm after he retrieves the rebound.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) rests his hand on Mykhailiuk's (DET) front and marginal contact occurs as Mykhailiuk starts his dribble.
Mykhailiuk (DET) hooks his off-arm around Caldwell-Pope (LAL) and initiates contact that affects Caldwell-Pope's ability to defend.
Plumlee (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it from Davis (LAL) before incidental arm contact occurs thereafter.
Wright (DET) and Schroder (LAL) come together as they cross half-court and marginal contact occurs as they separate.
Davis (LAL) and Plumlee (DET) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Davis (LAL) firms up in his screening position following the hand-off and absorbs the contact made with Grant (DET).
Davis (LAL) and Grant (DET) engage and disengage with one another as Davis rolls toward the lane following the expiration of the pick.
Jackson (DET) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before attempting the shot.

Schroder (LAL) is retreating in his defensive position and absorbs the body contact made with Jackson (DET) after his gather. Schroder then brings his arm down slightly and brushes Jackson's off-arm during the driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Grant (DET) moves alongside of James' (LAL) path to the basket and legally contests his driving shot attempt with Plumlee (DET).
Schroder (LAL) extends his arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Wright's (DET) front as they move over the pick.
As Davis (LAL) extends his arm backwards to defend the pass, marginal contact occurs with Plumlee's (DET) right arm.
Grant (DET) trails Caldwell-Pope (LAL) in transition and marginal contact occurs during Caldwell-Pope's dunk attempt.
Grant (DET) establishes himself in a screening position with his hands slightly extended outward and absorbs the contact made with Schroder (LAL).
James (LAL) extends his forearm into Grant's (DET) side and initiates contact during the driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another as they move along the perimeter.
Davis (LAL) rests his hands on Grant's (DET) backside as he sets the pick and releases as marginal contact occurs.
Plumlee (DET) extends his arm forward and some contact occurs with James' (LAL) front as he drives toward the lane, and the contact is marginal.

Replay review of the foul called on Plumlee (DET) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Plumlee swipes down and cleanly dislodges the ball before incidental contact occurs with James (LAL) thereafter.
James (LAL) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two steps before attempting the shot.
Wright (DET) and Schroder (LAL) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another following the expiration of the pick.
Davis (LAL) brings his arm down and initiates contact with Grant's (DET) left arm after his gather.
Schroder (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Grant's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact.
Jackson (DET) contests Davis's (LAL) dunk attempt at the rim and marginal contact with Davis's arm occurs.
Jackson (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in James' (LAL) path and does not deliver the contact.
James (LAL) makes contact with the ball before incidental body contact occurs with Grant's (DET) backside as he receives the pass.

James (LAL) brings his hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Grant's (DET) front after his gather. James then makes incidental "high-five" contact with Grant after the release of the driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (LAL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Davis (LAL) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly deflects the ball as Grant (DET) is passing.
Kuzma (LAL) extends his hand forward and marginal contact occurs with Wright's (DET) front during the drive.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it from Grant (DET) before incidental contact occurs.
Davis (LAL) maintains legal guarding position and absorbs the body contact made with Plumlee (DET) during the drive.
Plumlee (DET) goes to, not through, Davis' (LAL) space as contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Correctly called 24 second violation on DET.
Schroder (LAL) and Grant (DET) engage and disengage with one another as the pick is set.
Wright (DET) makes contact with the ball and the part of Schroder's (LAL) hand that is on the ball at the end of the drive.
Plumlee (DET) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Plumlee (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Davis' (LAL) path following the hand-off and does not deliver the contact.
Grant (DET) commits a take foul on Caruso (LAL).
Davis (LAL) moves alongside Mykhailiuk's (DET) path and absorbs the body contact made at the end of the drive.
Plumlee (DET) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Plumlee (DET) is jumping to the side of James (LAL) and would avoid James' right foot if he did not extend it forward to initiate the marginal contact.
Caruso (LAL) has his hand rested on Jackson's (DET) left hip and marginal contact occurs as Jackson trips over his right foot.
James (LAL) extends his forearm and initiates contact with Grant's (DET) lower body as he is airborne, affecting his jump shot attempt.
Wright (DET) makes contact to Schroder (LAL) attempting to commit a take foul.
Jackson (DET) commits a take foul on Schroder (LAL). After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined the play did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) and Mykhailiuk (DET) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Plumlee (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (LAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) is moving toward Plumlee (DET) as marginal body contact occurs during Plumlee's upward shooting motion.
Mykhailiuk (DET) commits a take foul on Schroder (LAL).
Bey (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Caruso's (LAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Schroder (LAL) maintains a rested hand on Grant's (DET) front as marginal contact occurs during Grant's upward shooting motion.
